<div class="w3-content w3-container w3-padding-64">
  <h3 class="w3-center">About Institution</h3>
  <p>Annamalai University established by The Annamalai University Act, 1929, is the only unitary, residential, multi-faculty Univarsity in the state of Tamil Nadu with 10
  faculties and 52 departments of Study. The Annamalai University Campus is located very close to the famous pilgrimage town of Chidambaram, which is the adobe of the cosmic dancer,
  Lord Nataraja. The campus is spread over an area of about 1000 acres in a sylvan setting. Maintaining a wide spectrum of faculties that include Engineering and Technology, Medicine, Dentistry , Agriculture,
Education, Science, Marine Science, Arts, Fine Arts and Indian Languages, the university also offers diverse programmes of study through its Directorate of Distance Education. The University celebrated its platinum Jubilee during the year 2004 and organised the 
94th Indian Science Congress in the year 2007. </p>
<p>
<h3 class="w3-center">About Department</h3>
  <p>The UG programme Electronics and Communication Engineering (B.E.) and PG programme Communication System (M.E.) were started in the year 2002 and 2014 respectively under the Department of 
  Electrical Engineering. The Department is boosted with well established laboratories and has good collection of books in its library. The Department of Electronics and Communication Engineering offers UG, PG programmes encapsulating the emerging trends of ECE and Ph.D
  programme in a variety of diversified domains. The Faculty members have expertise in almost all domains of ECE, paving way for the researchers to carry out their research in any challenging domain of ECE. 
  Further, the faculty brings State-of-the-Art, Reasearch Development, and Design Experience into the classroom.</p>
<p>
</div>


